properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 3:08AM CST until January 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Slick Travel With a Light Wintry Mix Today...

.A light wintry mix of freezing rain and snow will develop by mid
morning, continuing into the afternoon before quickly diminishing
by late afternoon. Roads will likely become slick with a light
glazing of ice. If you have travel planned today, slow down and be
prepared for slippery roads.

* WHAT...Light mixed precipitation expected. Total ice
accumulations of up to one tenth of an inch.

* WHERE...Taylor County.

* WHEN...From 8 AM this morning to 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained from Wisconsin 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 6 PM CST THIS EVENING
